The people have 4 different jobs:  bartender, dancer, dressmaker, musician
There are 4 different nationalities: american, dutch, french, turkish
4 different games are played: domino, backgammon, monopoly, bridge
 1. the musician is on the right of the dancer##1
 2. the french is on the left of the person playing backgammon##1
 3. the dressmaker is on the left of the person playing domino##1
 4. the person driving the snowmobile is on the right of the person playing bridge##1
 5. the person driving the motorbike is on the right of the owner of the pony##1
 6. the turkish is the dressmaker##1
 7. the american is the dancer##1
 8. the musician is between the dressmaker and the person driving the scooter##2
 9. the owner of the frog is on the far left##1
10. the owner of the pony is between the person driving the scooter and the owner of the chinchilla##2
11. the person driving the scooter is on the left of the person driving the snowmobile##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |       1       |      2      |      3      |     4     |
| Transport          | scooter       | snowmobile       | motorbike | airplane    |
| Pet         | frog     | pony | chinchilla | horse     |
| Job           | dancer        | musician    | dressmaker  | bartender |
| Nationality   | american      | french      | turkish     | dutch     |
| Game         | bridge | monopoly      | backgammon    | domino |

